<subSubSection id="C335652C2B47FFA1FF08A9C3FD06FC2F" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B9036A72B47FFA1FF08A9C3FD06FC2F" blockId="10.[151,1128,666,1553]" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">
<emphasis id="B95BEAB52B47FFA1FF08A9C3FEA2FD0F" bold="true" box="[151,267,666,689]" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Length 6.8–8.0 mm. Head black with faint greenish lustre, pubescent and coarsely punctured. Pronotum brown with yellowish brown borders, pubescent and coarsely punctured. Elytra brownish yellow, with odd intervals reddish brown, brown or black, at least towards end of the dark markings, sometimes even red at beginning (especially in interval VII). The dark markings longest in intervals I and III, distinctly shorter in V, and again shorter in VII. Interval IX dark in its whole length. Even intervals always light brownish yellow, but somewhat darker towards end. Apex always yellow. Legs, palpi and antennomeres yellow, from antennomere four on sometimes a bit darker.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C335652C2B47FFA0FF08A8C3FD0AFD8D" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="112" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9036A72B47FFA1FF08A8C3FC88FBAF" blockId="10.[151,1128,666,1553]" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">
<emphasis id="B95BEAB52B47FFA1FF08A8C3FEB0FC0F" bold="true" box="[151,281,922,945]" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Comments.</emphasis>
The following specimens were studied: one from 
<collectingCountry id="F33876372B47FFA1FCA6A8C3FC28FC0F" box="[825,897,922,945]" name="Kenya" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Kenya</collectingCountry>
, two from Transvaal, one from 
<collectingCountry id="F33876372B47FFA1FF63A8E3FEC1FC6F" box="[252,360,954,977]" name="Botswana" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Botswana</collectingCountry>
, one from 
<collectingCountry id="F33876372B47FFA1FE48A8E3FDE0FC6F" box="[471,585,954,977]" name="Zimbabwe" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Zimbabwe</collectingCountry>
(these specimens should refer to the nominotypical form), one from the 
<typeStatus id="549488052B47FFA1FEEBA883FE0BFC4F" box="[372,418,986,1009]" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">type</typeStatus>
locality of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D242B47FFA1FDBFA883FC38FC4F" authority=": Mts Mabla" authorityName="Mts Mabla" box="[544,913,986,1009]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Platymetopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="figuratus" subSpecies="somalicus">
<emphasis id="B95BEAB52B47FFA1FDBFA883FCA4FC4F" box="[544,781,986,1009]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">P. figuratus somalicus</emphasis>
: Mts Mabla
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry id="F33876372B47FFA1FC3FA883FC56FC4F" box="[928,1023,986,1009]" name="Djibouti" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Djibouti</collectingCountry>
), and one from 
<collectingCountry id="F33876372B47FFA1FF4EA8A3FEB7FBAF" box="[209,286,1018,1041]" name="Yemen" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Yemen</collectingCountry>
, which also should be the subspecies 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D242B47FFA1FD30A8A3FCB3FBAF" authorityName="Basilewsky" authorityYear="1948" box="[687,794,1018,1041]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Amblystomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="somalicus">
<emphasis id="B95BEAB52B47FFA1FD30A8A3FCB3FBAF" box="[687,794,1018,1041]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">somalicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9036A72B47FFA1FF2AAF43FBA5FB2F" blockId="10.[151,1128,666,1553]" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">
According to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBE4B562B47FFA1FEDAAF43FDA6FB8F" author="BASILEWSKY P." box="[325,527,1050,1073]" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" pagination="209 - 227" refId="ref7095" refString="BASILEWSKY P. 1948: Coleopteres harpalides nouveaux du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle. Revue Francaise d'Entomologie 14: 209 - 227." type="journal article" year="1948">BASILEWSKY (1948)</bibRefCitation>
the nominotypical form from southwest and 
<collectingCountry id="F33876372B47FFA1FC7AAF43FBCFFB8F" box="[997,1126,1050,1073]" name="South Africa" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">south Africa</collectingCountry>
is never longer than 
<quantity id="4CD79B422B47FFA1FEEEAF63FE6AFBEF" box="[369,451,1082,1105]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" unit="mm" value="6.5">6.5 mm</quantity>
and the dark markings are brown. In the subspecies 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D242B47FFA1FC6AAF63FBC9FBEF" authorityName="Basilewsky" authorityYear="1948" box="[1013,1120,1082,1105]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Amblystomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="somalicus">
<emphasis id="B95BEAB52B47FFA1FC6AAF63FBC9FBEF" box="[1013,1120,1082,1105]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">somalicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the specimens from 
<collectingCountry id="F33876372B47FFA1FEEEAF03FE63FBCF" box="[369,458,1114,1137]" name="Djibouti" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Djibouti</collectingCountry>
are longer, the brown colour of the markings is turning into a dark metallic green, and the punctation of the head, pronotum and elytra is weaker.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9036A72B47FFA1FF2AAFC3FD9EFAEF" blockId="10.[151,1128,666,1553]" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">
The specimen studied from 
<collectingCountry id="F33876372B47FFA1FE42AFC3FD8AFB0F" box="[477,547,1178,1201]" name="Kenya" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Kenya</collectingCountry>
is 7.0 mm long; the ones from Transvaal, identified by Basilewsky, are 6.5 and 7.0 mm long, with a very faint greenish lustre; the one from 
<collectingCountry id="F33876372B47FFA1FB91AFE3FF19FB4F" name="Botswana" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Botswana</collectingCountry>
is 
<quantity id="4CD79B422B47FFA1FF4FAF83FE88FB4F" box="[208,289,1242,1265]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.3" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" unit="mm" value="7.3">7.3 mm</quantity>
long with brown markings, and the specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="F33876372B47FFA1FCD2AF83FC16FB4F" box="[845,959,1242,1265]" name="Zimbabwe" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Zimbabwe</collectingCountry>
is 
<quantity id="4CD79B422B47FFA1FC41AF83FB99FB4F" box="[990,1072,1242,1265]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" unit="mm" value="7.5">7.5 mm</quantity>
long with a faint greenish lustre on the dark markings of the elytra. The specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="F33876372B47FFA1FB91AFA3FBCEFAAF" box="[1038,1127,1274,1297]" name="Djibouti" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Djibouti</collectingCountry>
is 
<quantity id="4CD79B422B47FFA1FF2EAE43FEABFA8F" box="[177,258,1306,1329]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" unit="mm" value="8.5">8.5 mm</quantity>
long, its intervals are brown without greenish lustre. The specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="F33876372B47FFA1FB83AE43FBCFFA8F" box="[1052,1126,1306,1329]" name="Yemen" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Yemen</collectingCountry>
mainland is 9.0 mm long and greenish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9036A72B47FFA1FF2AAE03FBC1FA6F" blockId="10.[151,1128,666,1553]" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">
In the Socotran specimens, all between 6.8 and 8.0 mm long, the dark markings are brown with a hardly visible faint metallic coppery lustre. The punctation of the pronotum in these specimens, and in the specimens from 
<collectingCountry id="F33876372B47FFA1FD9BAEC3FDE4FA0F" box="[516,589,1434,1457]" name="Yemen" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Yemen</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F33876372B47FFA1FDE0AEC3FD7EFA0F" box="[639,727,1434,1457]" name="Somalia" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Somalia</collectingCountry>
, seems a little less dense and less deep than in the African specimens. Also the punctation of the elytral intervals seems a little vaguer.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9036A72B47FFA0FF2AAE83FE45FE8D" blockId="10.[151,1128,666,1553]" lastBlockId="11.[113,1092,220,595]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="112" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">
That means that the differential characteristics mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBE4B562B47FFA1FCD2AE83FBB3FA4F" author="BASILEWSKY P." box="[845,1050,1498,1521]" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" pagination="209 - 227" refId="ref7095" refString="BASILEWSKY P. 1948: Coleopteres harpalides nouveaux du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle. Revue Francaise d'Entomologie 14: 209 - 227." type="journal article" year="1948">BASILEWSKY (1948)</bibRefCitation>
do not always apply, perhaps except for punctation. Also the East African, Yemeni and Socotran specimens, on average, are longer than the South African specimens. There seems to be no difference in the aedeagi of all the studied specimens. The taxonomic status of both subspecies needs a more comprehensive study.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9036A72B46FFA0FF0FAA65FD0AFD8D" blockId="11.[113,1092,220,595]" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">
<bibRefCitation id="EFBE4B562B46FFA0FF0FAA65FEE3FEED" author="ANDREWES H. E." box="[144,330,316,339]" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" pagination="223 - 251" refId="ref7029" refString="ANDREWES H. E. 1924: Descriptions of some new Carabidae from Ceylon (Part. I.). Spolia Zeylanica 12: 223 - 251." type="journal article" year="1924">ANDREWES (1924)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D242B46FFA0FE23AA65FCEDFEED" authority="Andrewes, 1924" authorityName="Andrewes" authorityYear="1924" box="[444,836,316,339]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Platymetopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pictus">
<emphasis id="B95BEAB52B46FFA0FE23AA65FD3AFEED" box="[444,659,316,339]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Platymetopus pictus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFBE4B562B46FFA0FD08AA65FCEDFEED" author="ANDREWES H. E." box="[663,836,316,339]" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" pagination="223 - 251" refId="ref7029" refString="ANDREWES H. E. 1924: Descriptions of some new Carabidae from Ceylon (Part. I.). Spolia Zeylanica 12: 223 - 251." type="journal article" year="1924">Andrewes, 1924</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F33876372B46FFA0FC1BAA65FC7DFEED" box="[900,980,316,339]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Ceylon</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F33876372B46FFA0FC42AA65FBBDFEED" box="[989,1044,316,339]" name="India" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">India</collectingCountry>
and also from 
<collectingCountry id="F33876372B46FFA0FF41AA05FE85FECD" box="[222,300,348,371]" name="Yemen" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Yemen</collectingCountry>
. As for its pattern of the elytra the author points out the similarity with 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D242B46FFA0FBB2AA05FF78FE2D" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1848" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Platymetopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="figuratus">
<emphasis id="B95BEAB52B46FFA0FBB2AA05FF78FE2D" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">P. figuratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, without mentioning differences between the two species. Also, the description matches completely the nominotypical subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D242B46FFA0FD24AAC5FC9EFE0D" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1848" box="[699,823,412,435]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Platymetopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="figuratus">
<emphasis id="B95BEAB52B46FFA0FD24AAC5FC9EFE0D" box="[699,823,412,435]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">P. figuratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The 
<typeStatus id="549488052B46FFA0FCE5AAC5FC1BFE0D" box="[890,946,412,435]" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">types</typeStatus>
of both taxa should be compared, but it is highly probable that specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D242B46FFA0FCB7AAE5FC2AFE6D" authorityName="Andrewes" authorityYear="1924" box="[808,899,444,467]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Platymetopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pictus">
<emphasis id="B95BEAB52B46FFA0FCB7AAE5FC2AFE6D" box="[808,899,444,467]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">P. pictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F33876372B46FFA0FC5AAAE5FBA6FE6D" box="[965,1039,444,467]" name="Yemen" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Yemen</collectingCountry>
will turn out to be 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D242B46FFA0FE8FAA85FE56FE4D" box="[272,511,476,499]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Platymetopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="figuratus" subSpecies="somalicus">
<emphasis id="B95BEAB52B46FFA0FE8FAA85FE56FE4D" box="[272,511,476,499]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">P. figuratus somalicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(no relevant differences could be found between the specimens from 
<collectingCountry id="F33876372B46FFA0FEBAAAA5FED0FDAD" box="[293,377,508,531]" name="Yemen" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Socotra</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F33876372B46FFA0FE1BAAA5FE67FDAD" box="[388,462,508,531]" name="Yemen" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Yemen</collectingCountry>
mainland, and 
<collectingCountry id="F33876372B46FFA0FDE7AAA5FD6CFDAD" box="[632,709,508,531]" name="Eritrea" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Eritrea</collectingCountry>
), or even 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D242B46FFA0FCAEAAA5FC24FDAD" authorityName="Andrewes" authorityYear="1924" box="[817,909,508,531]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Platymetopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pictus">
<emphasis id="B95BEAB52B46FFA0FCAEAAA5FC24FDAD" box="[817,909,508,531]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">P. pictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may represent a senior subjective synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D242B46FFA0FE2EA945FD35FD8D" box="[433,668,540,563]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Platymetopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="figuratus" subSpecies="somalicus">
<emphasis id="B95BEAB52B46FFA0FE2EA945FD35FD8D" box="[433,668,540,563]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">P.figuratus somalicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C335652C2B46FFA0FFEEA965FCE9FDED" box="[113,832,572,595]" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B9036A72B46FFA0FFEEA965FCE9FDED" blockId="11.[113,1092,220,595]" box="[113,832,572,595]" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">
<emphasis id="B95BEAB52B46FFA0FFEEA965FEADFDED" bold="true" box="[113,260,572,595]" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Distribution.</emphasis>
Eritrea, Djibouti. 
<emphasis id="B95BEAB52B46FFA0FE59A965FCE9FDED" bold="true" box="[454,832,572,595]" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">
First record from 
<collectingCountry id="F33876372B46FFA0FD0BA965FC92FDED" box="[660,827,572,595]" name="Socotra Island" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Socotra Island</collectingCountry>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
